      h3 The Laptop as Dwelling
      p.subtext Realtime Electronics and Computer Sounds, 2016
      p In this piece I sonify the innards of the laptop with a coil microphone.  I wanted to examine an idea, borrowed from G. Bach, that a laptop can be a space we inhabit. As he says: “For Musician and audience alike, the laptop is interior space because we believe it to be so.” A side interest in the piece was to travel on a spectrum from noise to melody, tuning the laptop noise to different notes as I go along.  
      p <iframe width="100%" height="20" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/248210199&amp;color=95bcda&amp;inverse=true&amp;auto_play=false&amp;show_user=false"></iframe>
    
